## This userguide on how to install python on ubuntu

See this link >> https://phoenixnap.com/kb/how-to-install-python-3-ubuntu (python)
See this link >> https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-install-pip-on-ubuntu-18.04/ (pip)
1. python --version
2. sudo apt update
3. sudo apt install software-properties-common
4. sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa
5. sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa
6. sudo apt install python3.8 or 2.6
7. python --version
8. Install PIP 
   a. sudo apt install python3-pip (python3)
   b. sudo apt install python-pip (python2)
